{"word":"H3256 - יָסַר - yâçar - yaw-sar' - Bind","slug":"H3256","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יָסַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>yâçar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yaw-sar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bind"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D9;&#x05E1;&#x05E8; - ya&#x0302;sar</b> - <i>yaw-sar'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>chastise</i>, literally (with blows) or figuratively (with words); hence to <i>instruct: - </i>bind, chasten, chastise, correct, instruct, punish, reform, reprove, sore, teach."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3250\">H3250</a>, <a href=\"#/H4148\">H4148</a>, <a href=\"#/H4561\">H4561</a>"}]}